    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>pork mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!), <strong>chipotle paste</strong> (can’t handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>chopped coriander stems</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> in a bowl, then divide the mixture into 3 per person and shape them into meatballs</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the meatballs and cook for 2 min on each side or until browned</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1696851186942-x200.jpg",
